CONDITION: Line_Singularity
CONDTYPE: over lines
CONDMESHTYPE: over nodes
QUESTION: Ungaged_layers#CB#(1,2,3,4,5,6)
VALUE: 1
HELP: Number of ungaged layers around a line:\n- In the regularized formulations, the divergence term of the elements\n   inside the ungauged layers is removed.\n- In the LL2P formulations, both the divergence term and the bubble\n   contribution of the elements inside the ungauged layers are removed.
END CONDITION

CONDITION: Perfect_Electric_Conductor_(PEC)
CONDTYPE: over surfaces
CONDMESHTYPE: over face elements
QUESTION: n_x_E_=#CB#(0.0)
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: - For E-field formulations, it imposes n x E = 0 on the surface.\n- For A-V potential formulations, it sets n x A = 0 and V = 0 on the surface.\n- For edge-stabilized formulations, it additionally sets the Lagrange multiplier\n   equal to zero on the surface.
END CONDITION

CONDITION: Perfect_Magnetic_Conductor_(PMC)
CONDTYPE: over surfaces
CONDMESHTYPE: over face elements
QUESTION: n_._E_=#CB#(0.0)
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: - For regularized and LL2P E-field formulations, it imposes n . E = 0 on the surface.\n- For regularized and LL2P A-V potential formulations, it sets n . A = 0 on the surface.\n- It is redundant for double-curl edge formulations.\n- This condition is specifically designed for symmetry surfaces.
END CONDITION

CONDITION: Transversal_Electric_Condition_(TEC)
CONDTYPE: over surfaces
CONDMESHTYPE: over face elements
QUESTION: n_._E_=#CB#(0.0)
VALUE: 0.0
HELP: - For regularized and LL2P E-field formulations, it imposes n . E = 0 on the surface.\n- For regularized and LL2P A-V potential formulations, it sets n . A = 0 on the surface.\n- It is redundant for double-curl edge formulations.\n- This condition is specifically designed for waveguide port surfaces.
END CONDITION

CONDITION: Periodic_Boundary_Condition_(PBC)
CONDTYPE: over surfaces
CONDMESHTYPE: over face elements
QUESTION: Face#CB#(Front,Back,Right,Left)
VALUE: Front
HELP: It enforces equal fields (with a phase difference) on two \nseparate surfaces:\n\n- "Front-Back" surfaces must lie parallel to the XY-plane.\n\n- For cyclic periodic symmetry, "Left" surface must be \n   positioned in the 00-YZ plane and the axis of rotation \n   must align with the Z-axis.\n\n- Set the symmetry type and phase difference between \n   surfaces in "Solving parameters" -> "Geometry".\n\n- If PBCs are required only between parallel surfaces with  \n   no phase difference, separate contact volume elements  \n   can be used as an equivalent alternative.\n 
END CONDITION

